<br>
1) Wizards suffer real problems when dealing with high con mobs who's resists suck, and I mean from ALL levels, not just 50+.<br>
2) Bane spells seem a superb idea (bar the components sorry don't see wizzies USING components ever, masters of energy). They are restricted to a certain type of mob, but uber powerful.<br>
<br>
Ok so would questable, mob dropped and research spells of those types, from say lvl 20+ be interesting and USEFUL to wizards?<br>
Examples:<br>
1) Archmagi in Lower Guk drops a rare spell, Froglock Bane lvl 40, does 50% more damage, less aggro than best nuke of that level, affects only live froglocks.<br>
2) At lvl 20 a quest results in Inferno Lure. Same mana/damage as typical spell but DOUBLE the cast time. (i.e. with lures, wouldn't making the CAST TME slow, but having the mana ratio similar to normal be more useful?)<br>
3)  A research lure knockback spell at lvl 50ish, so research is useful again, and push spells rule for disrupting high lvl casters. This spell would have a fast cast time (2 sec), cost 150 mana?<br>
<br>
<br>
Any thoughts wizards ?<!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
